{"_id":"C5nb9mm7Z9dqoxFB","name":"Mirage Mystery","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/spells/air-walk.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You gaze into the fabric of the dreams and wishes of mortals. By tugging at these threads, you change what others perceive as real. You may draw power from deities of fate and dream such as Desna or Pharasma or instead draw fickle power from fey lords and Outer Gods. For reasons theorized by the followers of Nethys, oracles of mirage are most commonly found among the desert-dwelling Osirians.</p>\n<p><strong>Mystery Benefit:</strong> You see echoes that still linger from the First World and can use these to alter your visage. You never take penalties for attempting to take a disguise of a different ancestry, age and so on, as long as the disguised form is appropriate for your size.</p>\n<p><strong>Trained Skills</strong> Deception and Occultism</p>\n<p><strong>Granted Cantrip</strong> @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.4gBIw4IDrSfFHik4]{Daze}</p>\n<p><strong>Revelation Spells</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>initial:</strong> @Compendium[pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-spells.ldKl3Lh0gFdgJPAy]{Vainglory}</li>\n<li><strong>advanced:</strong> @Compendium[pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-spells.fWtmRO2hAWEBOF0k]{Tarnish the Mind}</li>\n<li><strong>greater:</strong> @Compendium[pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-spells.h8xblrhF1hFXSY62]{Visions Materialized}</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Related Domains</strong> delirium, dreams</p>\n<h3>Curse of the Desert's Dream</h3>\n<p>The glimpses you catch of other worlds, of potentials and possibilities, allow you to reshape the nature of reality but leave you unsure as to what is true and what is false. Colors around you are unusually vivid, and you murmur to yourself in reply to unheard questions. Fine sand, manifesting from other planes, often gets caught in the folds of your clothes.</p>\n<p><strong>Minor Curse</strong> You lose touch with what is real as phantasms and illusory sprits occlude your vision. You take a -2 status penalty to all skill checks based on sight.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-effects.bgMVXTiQoiws4Brf]{Effect: Minor Curse of the Desert's Dream}</p>\n<p><strong>Moderate Curse</strong> You are unable to see the truth anymore and sand pours from your eyes instead of tears. You are @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.HL2l2VRSaQHu9lUw]{Fatigued} until you rest, and the penalty from your minor curse increases to -4. You must rest for 10 hours instead of 8, during which time your soul will reside in its own dreamscape. Your body will have no pulse and you cannot be woken by any magical or physical means. You can use the sand from your eyes to create small objects. This works like @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.TPI9fRCAYsDqpAe4]{Temporary Tool}, except the created object lasts for as long as you are suffering this moderate curse effect, or until you create a new object; at which point the previous object crumbles into sand.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-effects.HAs01cA3Jdqi7Y0t]{Effect: Moderate Curse of Ruination}</p>\n<p><strong>Major Curse (11th)</strong> The illusions that cloud your sight begin bleeding through, becoming momentarily real. An aura of riotous color and sand surrounds you in a 30-foot emanation, dealing [[/r 2d8 #negative]]{2d8 negative damage} (basic Will save) to all other creatures in the aura at the end of each of your turns. You are @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Dazzled]{Dazzled} and @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Slowed]{Slowed 1}, with no save.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-effects.CvndzMkpd2c5p7aU]{Effect: Major Curse of Ruination}</p>"},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":[],"rarity":{"value":"common"},"custom":""},"rules":[{"key":"PF2E.RuleElement.ActiveEffectLike","mode":"upgrade","path":"data.skills.dec.rank","value":1},{"key":"PF2E.RuleElement.ActiveEffectLike","mode":"upgrade","path":"data.skills.occ.rank","value":1}],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.692,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2021-11-20T03:07:06.827-05:00","version":{"schema":0.652,"foundry":"0.8.9","system":"2.19.0.9009"}}},"level":{"value":0},"featType":{"value":"bonus"},"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"vkXZ1CDW49ufIquY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-class-features.C5nb9mm7Z9dqoxFB"}}}
{"_id":"GtvQ2kzbkyZ4dkPX","name":"Arcane Thesis: Riffle Scroll Master","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/equipment/consumables/other-consumables/spell-scroll.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You have looked closely into the workings of riffle scrolls, and either through ease of use, or to help circumvent some personal condition that prevents you from casting naturally, have trained yourself in the use of these scrolls as your primary method of casting. You gain the @Compendium[pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-feats.h9rFEx4PU0eE0XmM]{Riffle Scroll Casting} Feat as a bonus feat. You can draw a riffle scroll as a free action, so long as your next action or actions are used to perform the Cast a Spell Activity using the drawn riffle scroll.</p>"},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":[],"rarity":{"value":"common"},"custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.692,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2021-11-20T03:07:06.829-05:00","version":{"schema":0.652,"foundry":"0.8.9","system":"2.19.0.9009"}}},"level":{"value":0},"featType":{"value":"bonus"},"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"vkXZ1CDW49ufIquY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-class-features.GtvQ2kzbkyZ4dkPX"}}}
{"_id":"MwH37WqVVMaOOz32","name":"Tragedy Muse","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/spells/alter-reality.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your muse is something beautiful that has been lost, driving you to protect others from such suffering or to inflict it upon your foes. If your muse is a creature, it might be lost comrades or a fallen hero; if a deity, it might be the dead god Aroden or the lost aspect of Zon-Kuthon, Dou-Bral. You gain the @Compendium[pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-feats.Si40Rty9ogMFOjiK]{Succor Song} feat and add @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.R8bqnYiThB6MYTxD]{Phantom Pain} to your spell repertoire.</p>"},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["bard"],"rarity":{"value":"common"},"custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.692,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2021-11-20T03:07:06.830-05:00","version":{"schema":0.652,"foundry":"0.8.9","system":"2.19.0.9009"}}},"level":{"value":0},"featType":{"value":"classfeature"},"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"vkXZ1CDW49ufIquY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-class-features.MwH37WqVVMaOOz32"}}}
{"_id":"oqoLhAh4af2qoQLd","name":"Apocalypse Mystery","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/spells/abyssal-wrath.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>With the death of prophecy, nothing is certain anymore. Old gods have died; new gods have risen. Horrors from the past have come to call; death and fire have rained from the sky! Only a madman would be blind to the signs! The End is nigh, you have seen it - the End of All Things! You may revere gods who embody this end, like Groetus or Rovagug, the Tian goddess Lady Nanbyo, or outer gods like Azathoth. Alternately, your power may well up from the endless destructive power of the Maelstrom or the Abyss.</p>\n<p><strong>Mystery Benefit</strong> Choose one type of energy at 1st level: acid, cold, electricity, fire, or negative energy. This is your apocalyptic energy. Once chosen this cannot be retrained. Whenever you cast a damaging divine spell, you may chose to convert half of the spell's damage to your apocalyptic energy type. If you choose negative energy, this energy never heals undead.</p>\n<p><strong>Trained Skill </strong>Intimidate</p>\n<p><strong>Granted Cantrip</strong> @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.60sgbuMWN0268dB7]{Telekinetic Projectile}</p>\n<p><strong>Revelation Spells </strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>initial:</strong> @Compendium[pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-spells.mobjCcIlbTOjja1z]{Doomsayer}</li>\n<li><strong> advanced:</strong> @Compendium[pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-spells.vFox6oFvJCYtCKOW]{Devastation}</li>\n<li><strong>greater: </strong>@Compendium[pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-spells.hwGQgxCrSt5yennL]{Calamity}</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Related Domains</strong> decay, destruction</p>\n<h3>Curse of Ruination</h3>\n<p>The power of the end times flowing from you destroys everything you touch. Weapons bend in your grasp, your armor hangs in tatters, and small items break everywhere you go.</p>\n<p><strong>Minor Curse </strong>Any items you hold are warped by destructive energy. For as long as you hold any item, and for one round thereafter, it gains the shoddy trait.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-effects.p4KyXS1zn2hQfsdU]{Effect: Minor Curse of Ruination}</p>\n<p><strong>Moderate Curse</strong> Your worn items are wrecked and torn; even magical protection is rent asunder. Any item bonus to your AC is reduced by 2, and any armor check penalties are increased by 2. You gain a +1 status bonus to attack rolls and spell DCs whenever you cast a divine spell capable of causing your apocalyptic energy's damage. You may use the Warp Weapon reaction.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-effects.HAs01cA3Jdqi7Y0t]{Effect: Moderate Curse of Ruination}</p>\n<p><strong>Major Curse</strong> Whenever you use a held item, make a <span data-pf2-check=\"flat\" data-pf2-traits=\"\" data-pf2-label=\"\" data-pf2-dc=\"5\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"owner\">Flat Check</span>. On a failed check, the item gains the broken condition before you use it. Your Warp Weapon reaction lasts until the end of the triggering creature's next round. You gain a +2 status bonus to attack rolls and spell DCs whenever you cast a divine spell that causes your apocalyptic energy's damage type. Any creature that touches you or attacks you with an unarmed attack or natural weapon takes 1d6 damage from your apocalyptic energy (basic Reflex save with a DC equal to your class DC).</p>\n<p>@Compendium[pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-effects.CvndzMkpd2c5p7aU]{Effect: Major Curse of Ruination}</p>"},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["oracle"],"rarity":{"value":"common"},"custom":""},"rules":[{"key":"PF2E.RuleElement.ActiveEffectLike","mode":"upgrade","path":"data.skills.itm.rank","value":1}],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.692,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2021-11-20T03:07:06.831-05:00","version":{"schema":0.652,"foundry":"0.8.9","system":"2.19.0.9009"}}},"level":{"value":0},"featType":{"value":"classfeature"},"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"vkXZ1CDW49ufIquY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-class-features.oqoLhAh4af2qoQLd"}}}
{"_id":"ySF67KIzaTuJwTLr","name":"Spiritism Methodology","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/spells/spirit-link.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You know that beyond your world, the world of the material, there is a world of spirits and phantoms that intersects your own. For those willing to see this world, many mysteries can be made clear and hidden knowledge acquired. You are one of those seekers of the sacred mysteries and have learned to speak and commune with those spirits who have seen and will see far beyond what mortals can. Your extensive study of the supernatural, cult rituals, and shamanism have opened your mind to new investigative approaches. You are trained in Occultism and gain the @Compendium[pf2e.feats-srd.lEgYzFHransLkSvI]{Schooled In Secrets} skill feat and gain the @Compendium[pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-actions.xv5kkmb344ZIxXUI]{Dynamic Mediumship} action.</p>"},"source":{"value":""},"traits":{"value":["investigator"],"rarity":{"value":"common"},"custom":""},"rules":[{"key":"PF2E.RuleElement.ActiveEffectLike","mode":"upgrade","path":"data.skills.occ.rank","value":1}],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.692,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2021-11-20T03:07:06.831-05:00","version":{"schema":0.652,"foundry":"0.8.9","system":"2.19.0.9009"}}},"level":{"value":0},"featType":{"value":"classfeature"},"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"vkXZ1CDW49ufIquY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf2e-wayfinder.wayfinder-class-features.ySF67KIzaTuJwTLr"}}}
